---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - PocketBurrito">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-gaming font-bold text-white mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-10">Last updated: February 19, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          By accessing or using PocketBurrito's services at pocketburrito.ca, billing.pocketburrito.ca, and panel.pocketburrito.ca (collectively, the "Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, do not use the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          PocketBurrito provides game server hosting services, including but not limited to: provisioning and managing dedicated game servers, providing a control panel for server management, and billing and account management. We support multiple game titles across various tiers and configurations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">3. Account Registration</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          To use the Service, you must create an account. You agree to provide accurate, current, and complete information during registration and to keep your account information updated. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activities that occur under your account.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>You must be at least 13 years of age to create an account</li>
          <li>One account per person; multiple accounts are not permitted</li>
          <li>You are responsible for all activity on your account</li>
          <li>Notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your account</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">4. Payment and Billing</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          Game server hosting is provided on a subscription basis. By purchasing a service, you agree to pay the fees associated with the plan you select. All prices are listed in Canadian Dollars (CAD) unless otherwise stated.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>Payments are processed through Stripe and/or PayPal</li>
          <li>Subscriptions renew automatically at the end of each billing period</li>
          <li>You may cancel your subscription at any time through the billing portal</li>
          <li>Failure to pay may result in suspension or termination of your service</li>
          <li>We reserve the right to change pricing with 30 days notice</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">5. Acceptable Use Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          You agree to use the Service only for lawful purposes and in accordance with these Terms. You agree not to use the Service to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>Host, distribute, or promote illegal content</li>
          <li>Run cryptocurrency miners, botnets, or any malicious software</li>
          <li>Use cheats, exploits, or hacks that violate game publishers' terms of service</li>
          <li>Attack, disrupt, or attempt to gain unauthorized access to other systems</li>
          <li>Consume excessive resources that degrade service for other customers</li>
          <li>Resell or redistribute server resources without authorization</li>
          <li>Host content that infringes on intellectual property rights</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">6. Server Resources and Limitations</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          Each game server plan includes specific resource allocations (RAM, CPU, disk space) as described on the pricing page. Your server is allocated the resources associated with your selected plan tier. Fair use policies apply to shared resources such as CPU and network bandwidth.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">7. Service Availability</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          We strive to maintain high availability for all services. However, we do not guarantee uninterrupted service. Scheduled maintenance will be announced in advance when possible. We are not liable for downtime caused by factors outside our control, including but not limited to DDoS attacks, upstream provider outages, or force majeure events.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">8. Data and Backups</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          While we make efforts to maintain server data, you are responsible for maintaining your own backups. We strongly recommend using the backup features available through the control panel. PocketBurrito is not responsible for data loss resulting from hardware failure, software issues, or account termination.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">9. Suspension and Termination</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your account and services at any time for violation of these Terms, non-payment, or any other reason at our sole discretion. Upon termination, your server data may be permanently deleted after a reasonable grace period.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>Services suspended for non-payment may be reactivated upon payment</li>
          <li>Services terminated for Terms violations are not eligible for refund</li>
          <li>You may request account deletion by contacting support</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, PocketBurrito shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including but not limited to loss of data, loss of profits, or business interruption, arising out of or in connection with the use of the Service. Our total liability shall not exceed the amount paid by you for the Service in the 12 months preceding the claim.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">11. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          We may update these Terms from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by posting the updated Terms on this page and updating the "Last updated" date. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">12. Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          If you have questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us through our
          <a href="https://billing.pocketburrito.ca/tickets/create" class="text-gaming-accent hover:text-gaming-purple transition">support ticket system</a>
          or join our <a href="https://discord.gg/gjjGWYY7" class="text-gaming-accent hover:text-gaming-purple transition">Discord community</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
